OL,3,CWhat are Henry VIII powers and why
OL,4,Cmight Keir Starmer use them?
OL,6,FWords by ITV News Producer, Kieran
OL,7,FCarter
OL,9,FThe government is considering making
OL,10,Fit easier to adopt EU laws, by passing
OL,11,Flegislation that would allow it to
OL,12,Fchange regulations without having to
OL,13,Fface full scrutiny from MPs.
OL,15,FThe move, part of Sir Keir Starmer's
OL,16,Freset of EU relations, would allow the
OL,17,FUK to quickly adapt to EU regulations
OL,18,Fon issues like food standards by
OL,19,Ftweaking UK law via secondary
OL,20,Flegislation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776161176
OL,3,CWhat are Henry VIII powers and why
OL,4,Cmight Keir Starmer use them?
OL,6,FThe move would allow new regulations
OL,7,Fto be approved through secondary
OL,8,Flegislation, which cannot be amended
OL,9,Fand usually does not need an official
OL,10,Fvote from MPs, under what are known as
OL,11,FHenry VIII powers.
OL,13,FSome view using those powers as
OL,14,Fcontroversial, voicing concerns the
OL,15,Fmove would bring the UK closer to
OL,16,Frejoining the single market, and
OL,17,Fpotentially leave the door open for
OL,18,Feven closer alignment with the EU than
OL,19,Fthat.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
