OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776161176
OL,3,CWhat are Henry VIII powers and why
OL,4,Cmight Keir Starmer use them?
OL,6,FBut what are Henry VIII powers and why
OL,7,Fare they so controversial? ITV News
OL,8,Fexplains.
OL,10,FWhat are Henry VIII powers?
OL,12,FThe power to amend Acts of Parliament
OL,13,Fby order, without scrutiny from MPs,
OL,14,Fis known as a "Henry VIII power" - a
OL,15,Fslightly tongue-in-cheek reference to
OL,16,Fthe 16th century monarch's supposed
OL,17,Fpenchant for legislating via royal
OL,18,Fproclamations, rather than through
OL,19,Fparliament.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776161176
OL,3,CWhat are Henry VIII powers and why
OL,4,Cmight Keir Starmer use them?
OL,6,FIn the UK, there are two types of
OL,7,Flegislation: primary and secondary.
OL,9,FMost bills are passed through primary
OL,10,Flegislation, where they go through a
OL,11,Flengthy process of scrutiny by both
OL,12,FMPs and the House of Lords.
OL,14,FBut with secondary legislation, once
OL,15,Fwritten by government ministers, laws
OL,16,Fmust either be accepted or rejected,
OL,17,Fand are not open to amendments or
OL,18,Fscrutiny.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776161176
OL,3,CWhat are Henry VIII powers and why
OL,4,Cmight Keir Starmer use them?
OL,6,FThat's where Henry VIII powers come
OL,7,Fin. These clauses allow ministers to
OL,8,Fchange or even scrap parts of existing
OL,9,Flaws using secondary legislation,
OL,10,Fsidestepping the full back-and-forth
OL,11,Fof parliamentary scrutiny that primary
OL,12,Flegislation would usually require.
OL,14,FThis form of secondary legislation is
OL,15,Ftypically used for routine updates and
OL,16,Fhas not been opposed in the House of
OL,17,FCommons since 1979.
OL,19,FWhy Henry VIII?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776161176
OL,3,CWhat are Henry VIII powers and why
OL,4,Cmight Keir Starmer use them?
OL,6,FThe nickname given to these laws comes
OL,7,Ffrom measures introduced by King Henry
OL,8,FVIII in 1539.
OL,10,FAt this time, Henry VIII introduced
OL,11,Fthe Statute of Proclamations, a law
OL,12,Fthat gave him the power to govern by
OL,13,Froyal decree, avoiding Parliamentary
OL,14,Fscrutiny entirely.
OL,16,FThough a different mechanism, changing
OL,17,Fthe law via secondary legislation in
OL,18,Fsuch a way that it avoids a vote by
OL,19,FMPs is often given the same name.
OL,21,FHow will the government use them?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776161176
OL,3,CWhat are Henry VIII powers and why
OL,4,Cmight Keir Starmer use them?
OL,6,FThe government intends to use these
OL,7,Fmeasures to make trade with the
OL,8,FEuropean Union easier.
OL,10,FIt will do this by keeping British
OL,11,Frules aligned with European ones, a
OL,12,Fprocess known as dynamic alignment.
OL,14,FThe legislation would allow laws
OL,15,Fconcerning areas where the UK has
OL,16,Fsigned a deal with the EU to be
OL,17,Fupdated without having to bring a
OL,18,Ffresh bill to parliament each time.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776161176
OL,3,CWhat are Henry VIII powers and why
OL,4,Cmight Keir Starmer use them?
OL,6,FThe prime minister said the changes
OL,7,Fwill only come into force if
OL,8,Fparliament passes the legislation,
OL,9,Fadding that a stronger relationship
OL,10,Fwith Europe is in the "UK's best
OL,11,Finterest".
OL,13,FHe said: "We're in a world where
OL,14,Fthere's massive conflict, great
OL,15,Funcertainty, and I strongly believe
OL,16,Fthat the UK's best interests are in a
OL,17,Fstronger, closer relationship with
OL,18,FEurope, whether that's defence and
OL,19,Fsecurity... energy, inevitably, and
OL,20,Falso, our economy."
OL,26,@rD@WOUsD@IO]uD@JOU|D@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
